}} 'Prochlorperazine' ('Compazine', 'Stemzine', 'Buccastem', 'Stemetil',
'Phenotil') is a dopamine (D2) receptor antagonist that belongs to the
phenothiazine class of antipsychotic agents that are used for the antiemetic
treatment of nausea and vertigo. It is also a highly potent typical
antipsychotic, 10-20x more potent than chlorpromazine. It is also used to treat
migraine headaches. Intravenous administration can be used to treat status
migrainosus.
